Defendant Michael A Griger in court.  Lindsey Hirt appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant waives his right to counsel and would like to accept the state's offer. Defendant enters a no contest plea to the charge. Court imposed the following sentence:

    The Defendant was given the following:

WITHHELD SENTENCE;

TERM OF PROBATION:  12 monoths concurrent

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  

*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;

RESTITUTION:  $200.00 ($30.00 to J. Patrick and $170.00 to Pawn America) (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

After six month of serving probation, defendant may petition the court for early termination upon all fine/costs being paid.
